SIMPLE: unsight
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unsight
<hw>Un*sight"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Doing or done
without sight; not seeing or examining.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unsight unseen</b></col>, <cd>a colloquial phrase,
denoting <xex>unseeing unseen</xex>, or <xex>unseen</xex> repeated; as,
to buy a thing <xex>unsight unseen</xex>, that is, without seeing
it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For to subscribe, <qex>unsight, unseen</qex>,⟦br⟧
To a new church discipline.</q> <rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was a great confluence of chapmen, that resorted from every
part, with a design to purchase, which they were to do
⟦ldquo⟧<qex>unsight unseen</qex>.⟦rdquo⟧</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unsightable</ent>⟦br⟧
